Originally ripped by Terminal Escape, posted on January 02, 2024 Description from Terminal Escape:
 Just...it's just a really nice sounding tape. That should be enough, right? (hint: it is) Extreme and ancient Pacific Northwest vibes on the debut OUTDATES recording, and the 4-track only adds an air of authenticity. Candilore's vocals sound completely at home warbling and wailing on tracks like "Sick Of Talkin'" and the entire tape just feels....warm and familiar. It's a short shot, but check "Taking Sides" (the shortest shot of them all) and tell me it's not worth it. MAKE WAY FOR OUTDATES
